r homes and orchards that sustained their livelihoods,\" according to NATO. \nBritish forces have denied that the Nimrod MR2 reconnaisance plane was shot down by the Taliban. Instead, they say, it was brought down by a technical fault. \nThe 4 Canadian deaths bring to 30 the number of Canadians killed since Canadian Forces joined the conflict in 2002. "}
